--------------------------- MODEL DEFINITION ------------------------------
CONSTANTS   L,      \     Number of leaders.                              )(
            Procs = {p_i | i <- INTEGERS},         \* Processes with priority 1 <= p < P are candidates for leader selection. *) ( * The set of all processes must be finite in this model.)       /   -------------------------- MV CONSTANT declarations    )
            Edges = {(p, q) |                     \      Numbering the edges from each process to its successors as e_1^i,...,e_{L+2}^i.  * Priority of edge i is p^(q + L - pi). *) (                /   CONSTANT definitions    )
            Leader = {l | l <- INTEGERS},         \     Initial leader selection must be consistent with the priority relation on Procs and Edges,       ______________________-                           * Each process has exactly two successors.  */) (          /   CONSTRAINT definition    )
